Duke of Wellington 's forces defeated and killed Tipu Sultan in Mysore in 1799 . 
  Troops returned to Britain with gold, jewellery, arms and armour and even Tipu's grand throne . 
  Collection of historic artefacts will go on sale at London auction house Bonhams . 
  Items collected over 30 years by British Tipu expert Robin Wigington are expected to fetch a total of £1million . 
  Sultan 's personal sporting gun is tipped to sell for £150,000 . 
 